{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 You might argue that if there is no real harm, there is no reason for the government to spend all of its resources on making sure that drugs don't get into the wrong hands."}
{'text': "Why are we legalizing drugs? Wouldn't it be better to start treating drugs like any other substance?"}

{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 There is a danger that legalizing drugs will lead to more use of illegal drugs, especially if the law enforcement isn't able to keep drugs out of the hands of children and young adults."}
{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 If people want to use and abuse drugs, let them. But don't expect the government to protect you from them."}
{'text': 'There is a huge difference between creating conditions that allow people to grow and sell their own crops, and completely legalizing and regulating the cultivation of drugs.'}

{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 Why shouldn't people whose minds are made up to commit crimes because of their views on politics be allowed to do so, while allowing those who want to be free to exercise their free will..."}
{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 Alcohol and tobacco are just drugs that are more difficult to get rid of, but that doesn't make them any less addictive."}
{'text': '\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 One of the hardest things to get people to understand is that marijuana is only slightly more dangerous than caffeine.'}
{'text': 'There are some people who will have a problem with this. For example, these are the people who end up in jail due to the War on Drugs.'}
{'text': "If there's a choice to be made between doing drugs or being a criminal, I'll take the drug every single time."}
{'text': 'If we legalize the use of drugs, those who abuse drugs would then also be able to legally buy them.'}

{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 I'm all for legalizing drugs, as long as the profits are put back into the community, and the government doesn't interfere in people's personal lives."}
{'text': 'Smoking or drinking is not the main problem with drugs.'}
{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 I don't think it's the government's place to decide what people can do with his/her own bodies."}

{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 Don't you think it might be a better idea to spend all of our money on making sure that criminals don't get drugs in the first place, instead of spending all of our money..."}
{'text': "I'm not a libertarian. I'm an anarchist. I do think that people should be allowed to use whatever substances they want as long as they don't harm themselves or others."}
{'text': "If we elect a government that doesn't give a hoot about people, then I guess the end of the world is nigh. Well, unless it's a techno-utopia, anyway."}
{'text': "I don't think we should make it any harder for people to use drugs than it already is, but I also don't think we should make it any easier for people to buy drugs than it already..."}

{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 Why is it that when it comes to other countries that have tried to legalize drugs, they're usually met with a lack of understanding from the American public?"}

{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 Well, wouldn't it be better if we cut off the flow of money from our government to criminals, allowing them to have a greater incentive to stop committing crimes?"}
{'text': 'The best solution would be to decriminalize all drugs, including marijuana, and legalize only those drugs which have been proven to be safe.'}
{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 I don't think we should legalize drugs at this time. It's too much of a slippery slope."}
{'text': '\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 If we legalized drugs, how would that effect our society? Would that mean less crime? Would that mean fewer overdoses?'}
{'text': 'What if instead of arresting people for using drugs, the government stops arresting people for using drugs? Then there would be no reason to arrest people for using drugs.'}

{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 If we legalize drugs now, we'll be at least a decade away from seeing a huge spike in the usage of drugs, which would in turn lead to higher costs for governmental services and..."}
{'text': 'The best solution to this problem is to legalize the cultivation of drugs and do away with the "illegal label.'}

{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 If drugs were legal, then people would be less likely to use them. I don't think it would take much to persuade people to stop using drugs."}

{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 Not only is it the best way to keep drug cartels out of the U.S., it's also one of the best ways to keep people from doing drugs."}

{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 That doesn't mean that all drugs should be legalized. There are still plenty of drugs that are far more harmful than the ones that are legal in the United States."}

{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 I am not a big fan of the design of this website. I think it's very dated. I feel like all of the information here is full of outdated information."}

{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 If you want to smoke weed, that's fine. Just don't be such a stoner that you'll destroy the planet and the lives of your loved ones."}

{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 There is no point in putting effort into legalizing a drug if the government won't make it easier for people to obtain these substances."}
{'text': '1) Do we really want to legalize every drug across the board? People have already begun to experiment with everything from MDMA (ecstasy) to LSD. It may be too late to stop them.'}
{'text': '\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 "What\'s the point? The problem with marijuana, alcohol, and tobacco is that they are highly addictive substances.'}

{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 If it's not illegal, then why don't law enforcement do something about it? I have no problem with legalizing drugs if a portion of the profits go back to society."}

{'text': "If we legalized and regulated the production and distribution of marijuana, we wouldn't need to police it anymore. The amount of drugs being trafficked into the United States would likely decrease."}
{'text': "It's easier to get young people to understand the benefits of drug use if they aren't burdened with the stigma of being a drug addict."}

{'text': '\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 If people really want to be free, they should be free to use whatever substances they want, without being arrested or imprisoned for doing so.'}
{'text': '2) There have been many people who have died as a direct result of drug use. What is your opinion on these deaths?'}
{'text': "This isn't about making it so that people can consume drugs. This is about making it so people won't be punished for doing so."}
{'text': "(2) People will still abuse drugs regardless of whether it's legal. As a society, we need to come to terms with the fact that some people will always have a desire to use drugs."}
{'text': "I was raised in the 1960s and 70s, so I'm somewhat of an old-school person."}
{'text': "I don't think it's the government's place to decide what people can do with their own bodies."}
{'text': 'It may seem like a lot of work, but in the long run this is really a small price to pay for reducing over-criminalization.'}

{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 The reason that so many people are against it is because they are afraid that it would increase drug use. That's simply not the case."}
{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 First, do you really want to have to buy your drugs from a street dealer? That's where the problems come in."}

{'text': '\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 As long as there is some type of regulation in place, people are going to get their drugs regardless of who has them or where they are found.'}
{'text': "If there are so many problems with the current system of prohibition, then why don't we take a step back and look at the whole issue from a different perspective?"}
{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 I don't know what the unintended consequences of legalization would be."}
{'text': "When the law has very little effect on society, it doesn't make any sense to keep enforcing the law."}
{'text': 'It would be better if people who wanted to use and abuse drugs legally could do so.'}

{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 It's a slippery slope. It's obvious that the more we legalize it, the more people will use and abuse it. However, that doesn't mean it should be legalized."}

{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 If drugs are legalized, we'll see an increase in crime related to drug use, which is already happening in other countries that are legalizing drugs."}

{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 I'm sure that if the government decriminalized all drugs and put some form of regulation in place, the amount of illegal drugs in the United States would decrease dramatically."}
{'text': '\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 Drug use is a serious problem in many countries around the world. It is a social problem as much as a physical one.'}
{'text': 'If there is no crime in the world, then why is it necessary to arrest so many people?'}

{'text': '\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 We realize that drug use is hugely widespread in America, and yet we are still spending so much money trying to deter people from using it.'}
{'text': 'Sure, people are going to find some new and novel ways to consume drugs, such as sniffing glue, drinking dirty water, or whatever they can come up with.'}
{'text': "The government shouldn't decide who can use drugs. That's a public health issue. But it's not a moral one either."}

{'text': '\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 What if instead of allowing drug users to use whatever substances they want, the government decided to provide them with free and unlimited access to education, health care, housing, and so forth?'}
{'text': "I don't want to be forced to use drugs, but at the same time, I don't want to have to face the consequences of having to use drugs if I decide to do so."}

{'text': '\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 One of the biggest problems with prohibition is that it is something that we as a society decide to do, not something that an individual decides to do.'}
{'text': "In the end, death comes because you are doing something against your own will. Don't try to blame the world for your lack of self-control."}
{'text': '\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 Something has to be done about the fact that the government is completely out of control when it comes to drug laws.'}

{'text': '\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 This is all assuming that legalizing drugs is an efficient way to address any of the problems listed above. In other words, how does this change the current state of affairs?'}
{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 If you legalize drugs, then you have to regulate them. It's the same thing as when alcohol was legalized in the US."}
{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 The more people who say they're against legalizing drugs, the more likely I am to start using drugs."}
{'text': "The first thing we need to do is to make it so that people aren't imprisoned for doing drugs."}
{'text': 'The US incarcerates more Americans per capita than any other country in the world except China.'}
{'text': "The reasons for marijuana legalization are actually pretty rational. Let's talk about why."}

{'text': '\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 Drug cartels are nothing more than a bunch of greedy assholes. They will do whatever they can to make as much money as they can.'}

{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 Instead of arresting people for using drugs, why don't we provide them with a place to use drugs safely, without fear of arrest?"}
{'text': '\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 Why is it that we have laws against smoking pot, but not against drunk driving, suicide, and murder?'}
{'text': "If there's no real harm, there's no real need for the government to spend all of its resources on making sure that drugs don't get into the wrong hands."}
{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 At this point, if the drug cartels don't have enough money to bribe the police, there is no point in arresting them."}

{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 If I were a politician or police official, I'd prefer that I didn't have to make the choice between drug users and drug dealers."}
{'text': "People who choose to use drugs will do so regardless of whether or not they're decriminalized. It is up to the user to decide whether or not they want to continue using drugs."}

{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 You see, when I was in school, the drug laws weren't nearly as strict as they are now. I didn't have to worry so much about breaking the law."}
{'text': '\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 We already have plenty of drugs that are far more harmful than the ones that are legal in the United States.'}

{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 When I was a kid in high school, the guys around my age were doing cocaine and/or pot pretty regularly. Today, they don't do either. Why?"}
{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 This isn't a complicated issue, but it's far too often avoided by those who should know better. It's time to face the facts."}
{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 We don't need to legalize drugs in order to prevent drug usage."}
{'text': '\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 The more people use drugs, the more likely it is that they will become addicts.'}

{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 Every person deserves to make his or her own decisions, but when it comes to drugs, there are so many factors that can affect someone's decision to use them."}
{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 The government has the right to make its own decisions, as long as those decisions don't infringe on the rights of others."}
{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 The government doesn't have any right to tell anyone what they can and can't do with their bodies."}
{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 Drug use is a choice. People who choose to use drugs will do so regardless of whether or not they're decriminalized."}
{'text': '\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 The issue of drug prohibition and the evils of the drug war have been debunked time and time again.'}

{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 It's a well known fact that most illegal drugs (with the exception of heroin) are far more dangerous than traditional pharmaceuticals like Vicodin and Percocet."}
{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 We need to deal with this issue in a different way than the way we've been dealing with it."}
{'text': '\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 Sooner or later, someone will find a better way to get the job done. No matter how much progress we make in the U.'}
{'text': "If you're going to do drugs, don't do drugs on the streets."}

{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 If these drugs are legal in the United States, why aren't they legalized everywhere else in the world? In other words, why isn't there a huge global movement to legalize drugs?"}

{'text': '\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 We do not need to imprison so many people for marijuana. Rather, we need to focus on the people who are supplying illegal drugs.'}
{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 The more people who say that they're against legalizing drugs, the more likely it is that I will start using drugs."}
{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 Let's not assume that people who smoke pot are necessarily any worse off than people who smoke cigarettes."}

{'text': '\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 I find it interesting that you\'re saying you don\'t want to "have to buy your drugs from a street dealer," but then admit you want to buy drugs from a street dealer.'}
{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 If you're a law-abiding citizen, you should feel free to use drugs."}
{'text': '\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 Being in favor of legalizing drugs is not the same thing as being pro-drugs.'}
{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 We've been living in a state of denial for too long. The fact that the U.S."}
{'text': '(3) Any law that allows the government to forbid certain activities in the name of health and safety must be upheld by the courts.'}
{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 The more people who say they're against legalizing drugs, the more likely I am to start using drugs."}

{'text': '\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 There is no such thing as a simple answer. Some people will always want to use illegal drugs, and there is no way for society to deal with that.'}
{'text': '\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 So far, the US government has never had any interest in helping people with their drug problems.'}

{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 The only thing that makes me comfortable with this stance is that it doesn't assume that recreational drug use is inherently negative."}

{'text': '\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 Even if we legalize drugs, some people will still use drugs. Some people are willing to take risks and do things against their own will.'}
{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 Think about it. How much worse would it be to have to die from an asthma attack because you couldn't afford an inhaler?"}

{'text': '\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 What if there was a way to make drugs less addictive? Maybe this could be achieved by increasing the tax on drugs so that they would be more expensive.'}
{'text': '\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 There is a difference between someone who wants to be free to use substances and someone who just wants to get high.'}

{'text': '\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 When you legalize drugs, you open the door for public health officials to say, "Hey, we know that coffee might make you feel a little more alert and energetic.'}

{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 Why are we focusing on marijuana and not cocaine, heroin, or methamphetamine? Isn't it possible that these other drugs are far more addictive than marijuana?"}
{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 The number one reason why people use drugs is because they don't want to admit that they have a problem."}
{'text': "The problem with legalization is that it could simply lead to more drug abuse, not less. But let's not forget that all drugs are not created equal."}

{'text': '\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 Is it really such a bad idea to legalize drugs? If it is, I hope we\'ll look back one day and say, "We should have done this a long time ago.'}

{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 If you're only going to legalize drugs if you're willing to let society become a dumping ground for drug addicts, then I'm not buying it."}
{'text': '\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 There has to be a way to get the profit back to society.'}
{'text': '\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 Any person over the age of 18 should have the right to choose whatever substance they want to use.'}
{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 It's time that we start treating drug addiction as a mental illness, not a crime."}

{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 By the time you finish reading this article, you'll probably have had a few drinks and caught up on the most recent episode of Game of Thrones."}
{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 If someone is going to do drugs, don't do them on the streets."}
{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 You can't legalize drugs and go without spending a lot of money on enforcement."}
{'text': '\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 By outlawing drugs, the government is no better off than if it had outlawed anything else.'}
{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 If you're going to legalize drugs, let's make sure we do it right."}
{'text': "1)\xa0 There are many studies showing that it doesn't create a big problem for society, and the same can be said for many other drugs, like alcohol."}
{'text': '\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 What if it was possible to make the non-addicting drugs even more potent? Then there would be no temptation to abuse them.'}

{'text': '\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 We need to keep in mind that marijuana is only one of many drugs, and that many of these drugs can be much more harmful than marijuana is.'}
{'text': '\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 As long as they are not hurting anyone else, why not allow them to use their drugs? Why not let them make their own decisions?'}
{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 Most drug users are addicts. I am not an addict. I'm not sure why you would argue that I am one."}

{'text': '\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 If we really want to help people with their drug problems, then we should focus on helping them find healthier ways to handle their drugs rather than going to all of the trouble of making them...'}
{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 I can't believe I'm saying this, but legalizing drugs is the worst thing that could possibly happen to the United States."}
{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 If no one is going to go to prison at the end of the day, then shouldn't we just legalize it? It's about time we did this."}
{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 If legalizing drugs isn't the best way to respond to the drug problem, then what is the best way?"}
{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 If there is a market for marijuana, then why shouldn't there be a market for heroin, cocaine, and other drugs as well?"}
{'text': "If it's not illegal, then why don't law enforcement do something about it? I have no problem with legalizing drugs if a portion of the profits go back to society."}
{'text': '\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 People who use drugs should be punished for their actions. No amount of taxation will make them stop.'}

{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 If we're going to legalize drugs, maybe we should legalize alcohol as well. Alcohol is far worse than any drug except maybe heroin."}

{'text': '\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 If all drugs are legalized, then those who wish to use drugs will be able to use them without fear of repercussion from the government.'}

{'text': '\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 First, I suspect that legalizing drugs would result in a reduction in the use of illegal drugs, so it would be a net positive for society.'}

{'text': '\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 There are still plenty of real problems with drug abuse. For example, high school kids are among the heaviest users of illegal drugs in the nation.'}
{'text': '\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 If the state of Colorado legalized marijuana, would that be a good thing?'}
{'text': "If you don't want anyone to use drugs, how about you stop using drugs?"}
{'text': "The more people who say they're against legalizing drugs the more likely I am to start using drugs."}

{'text': "If the goal is to protect the health and safety of the citizens, I don't believe that it's okay for the government to make the decisions regarding which drugs are illegal and which are legal."}

{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 Does anyone actually think that marijuana is less harmful than heroin, cocaine, meth, ecstasy, LSD, heroine, etc.? No, but that doesn't mean that we should legalize them all..."}

{'text': '1)\xa0 The government is already making millions of dollars off of us while we sleep. Do you really think they would stop if we started buying drugs from the government instead of the mafia?'}
{'text': '\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 Sure, legalizing drugs may make it easier for people to use them.'}
{'text': 'Reason #2: The state has no right to tell us what we can and cannot do with our bodies.'}
{'text': "If it's not illegal, then why don't law enforcement do something about it? I have no problem with legalization of drugs if a portion of the profits go back to society."}
{'text': '\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 Many of these drugs are highly addictive and can lead to very dangerous consequences if the user is not careful.'}
{'text': 'I think legalizing drugs is absolutely absurd.'}
{'text': '\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 If the government wants to legalize drugs, then it needs to put in place a system that ensures the safety of the users.'}
{'text': '\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 If we legalize drugs, it will result in fewer people being arrested for drug use.'}

{'text': '\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 I think legalizing drugs would be good for society, but I think it would also be good for society if everyone took drugs on their own terms.'}

{'text': '\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 Why not legalize drugs and then spend time and money trying to prevent drug usage instead of just making it easy for people to use?'}

{'text': '\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 The effects of legalized drugs would be the same as the effects of prohibition. The end result is the same. The decriminalization of drugs will not change the reality that prohibition has created.'}
{'text': "2)\xa0 The very fact that the government is making money off of people's bodies is proof that the government is not trying to help people. That's why we have laws."}

{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 Don't depend on legalization to make drugs more affordable. Legalization alone will not reduce the price of drugs in the United States."}
{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 I don't think that the government should decide whether a drug is illegal or not."}
{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 It's hard enough to get people to care about what goes on in our country."}
{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 Let's wait and see how this plays out before we move onto other issues."}

{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 Perhaps it's time we legalize drugs, just for a little while. Let's experiment with different ways of handling drugs. I mean, what's the harm in taking hallucinogens?"}
{'text': '1. There are other issues with drug use, such as violence, that aren\'t addressed in the black-and-white, "you\'re either with us or against us rhetoric surrounding drugs.'}

{'text': '\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 Addiction to any substance is very personal, so if we treat addiction as a mental illness rather than a crime, then we can help the thousands of kids who are suffering from it.'}
{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 If people are going to use drugs, why shouldn't they make their own decisions about how they use them?"}

{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 If it's not illegal, then why don't law enforcement do something about it? I have absolutely no problem with legalizing drugs if a portion of the profits go back to society."}
{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 As much as I'd like to say that I'm convinced that legalizing drugs is a good idea, I'm not."}

{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 It's easy for me to think that legalizing drugs is the best thing that could ever happen to the U.S., because I'm an addict myself."}

{'text': "It's time that we stop treating drug addiction as a mental illness, and start treating it as a criminal justice issue - those who commit crimes against others should be treated as criminals, not as mentally ill..."}
{'text': 'The laws that prohibit drugs are a far worse law than the ones that legalize them. While laws against drug use could be changed, so could laws against murder, theft, cheating, etc.'}

{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 In our current system, drug dealers are often the ones who go to jail. I can't help but feel that the government would be far better off if we legalized drugs."}
{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 Every law that allows the government to forbid certain activities should be upheld by the courts. It's just common sense."}

{'text': '\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 There\'s a small percentage of the population who are undoubtedly "addicts to drugs, and there\'s a large percentage of the population who are not addicts, but they\'re not living...'}
{'text': "The more people who say they're against legalization the more likely I am to start using drugs."}
{'text': "(3) I don't want to live my life in a world where I have to worry about being arrested every time I use a drug."}

{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 I don't think that legalizing drugs will solve anything. I also don't think it's right for the government to tell us what we can and can't do."}
{'text': "- If we're going to outlaw something, why not go all out and legalize it?"}

{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 If legalization of drugs did indeed lead to fewer people being arrested for drug usage, wouldn't this be a good thing? Wouldn't this be a victory for human rights?"}

{'text': '\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 Legalizing drugs will make it more difficult for the government to crack down on drugs. The government will have more resources available to deal with more crimes.'}
{'text': '\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 I would much rather live in a world where the state never enforced its laws against the use of drugs.'}
{'text': '\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 When it comes to drug policy, when it comes to drug use, people are both right and wrong.'}
{'text': '\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 Legalizing drugs also increases the availability of drugs.'}
{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 Have you ever wanted to smoke a joint and forget about everything else that's going on around you?"}

{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 Don't get me wrong, I'm not a huge fan of drugs in general. The only drugs I take are prescribed by my doctor and not because I want to."}
{'text': 'Reason #3: The war on drugs has caused more problems than it has solved (or at the very least not solved all of them) and is putting too many people in jail who should not be...'}
{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 If people are going to use drugs, why wouldn't they make their own decisions about how they use them?"}
{'text': "If you really want to change things, you need to first admit that drugs are a problem and recognize that it's going to be a problem for a very long time.\xa0 Just think about it."}

{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 What if there was a situation in which a person experienced a drug overdose, but was saved by a government-licensed drug dealer? Wouldn't this be a wonderful thing?"}

{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 Why are people going to jail for smoking pot? It's not like the government has ever been successful in curtailing the use of marijuana."}

{'text': '\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 Even though there are certain drugs that are illegal in most countries, there are still drugs that are far more harmful than the ones that are illegal in the United States.'}
{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 It's time to start treating drug addiction as a mental illness, not a crime."}
{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 If the legalization of drugs leads to less people being arrested for drug usage, wouldn't this be a good thing?"}
{'text': "If you really want to change things, you need to first admit that drugs are a problem and recognize that it's going to be a problem for a very long time."}
{'text': 'I think that the best way to deal with drug use is to legalize it, at least in the United States.'}
{'text': "If all drugs were made legal, then more people could get into drugs without having to break the law. If it were up to me, I'd legalize all drugs but marijuana."}
{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 We can't continue to treat drug addiction as a criminal justice issue.\xa0 It needs to be treated as a health issue."}
{'text': "Wouldn't it be great if we could end illegal drug use and drug dealing while simultaneously ending the war on drugs? The War on Drugs makes no sense at all."}
{'text': '\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 Even if it were possible to make the non-addicting drugs even more potent, then there would be no temptation to abuse them.'}

{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 I've already said many times that I think we should try to treat drug addiction as a mental illness, and not as a crime. This also applies to smoking marijuana."}

{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 What would the world be like if people didn't have any idea what a drug could be, or what a drug is actually doing to a person when it's being used recreationally?"}
{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 It's important to realize that the government does not have the right to tell us what to do with our bodies."}
{'text': "The government has no right to tell anyone what they can and can't do with their bodies."}
{'text': '\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 If we legalize drugs, all our current problems will go away.'}
{'text': '\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 If you legalize drugs, then the more you legalize drugs, the more people will start using drugs.'}

{'text': 'We already have the legal market for alcohol and tobacco. I think the point of legalizing drugs would be to create a regulatory system that would allow the production of legal substances that fall into those two categories.'}

{'text': '\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 A lot of drugs are not so much dangerous as they are addictive, and given enough time (a year or two at most), any individual could become dependent on a drug.'}
{'text': 'Legalizing drugs would be a win-win because it would help save lives, decrease crime rates, improve public health, and ultimately, make our country a safer place for everyone.'}
{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 When I say that legalizing drugs is a good idea, I don't mean that drugs should be legal."}
{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 It's time to treat addiction as a mental illness, not a crime."}

{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 There's a reason that millions of people have been addicted to drugs, and it's not because there was a shortage of drugs in the U.S. in the 80s."}
{'text': '\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 The vast majority of users of drugs do not become addicts, and the vast majority of addicts do not become users.'}
{'text': "It's going to take quite a bit of time before this even comes up, but it's only a matter of time before this starts happening."}

{'text': '\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 As long as drugs are illegal, they will continue to be used by people who want to get high, regardless of how they use them. This is a fact that cannot be denied.'}
{'text': '\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 It\'s worth noting that there are some people who abuse drugs regardless of whether or not they are "legalized (i.'}
{'text': '\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 We already have quite a few laws in place when it comes to drugs.'}

{'text': '\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 Treating drug addiction as a mental illness is exactly what we should be doing.\xa0 The idea that using a drug is bad because it gives you a "high is ridiculous.'}

{'text': '\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 Legalizing drugs will reduce the amount of money made off of them. There will be less profit to be made from these drugs, which will cause prices to go down for them.'}
{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 It's time to stop treating drug addiction as a crime and start treating drug addiction as a mental illness."}

{'text': '\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 Instead of banning certain types of drugs, we should legalize drugs that are proven to be harmful, like alcohol and tobacco, because those are proven to be harmful even without legalization.'}

{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 I don't have a problem if someone chooses to go out and smoke weed, but I do have a problem with people being put in jail for doing something completely legal under our current laws..."}
{'text': "Reason #3: The government has no right to tell me what I can and can't do with my body."}
{'text': '\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 If we were to legalize drugs, how would we do it? \xa0 What would the laws be? \xa0 How would we enforce it?'}
{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 The reason that more people are addicted to drugs isn't because there was a shortage of drugs in the U.S. in the 80s."}
{'text': '\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 How about we all just go ahead and legalize drugs and let people who want to use drugs do so on their own terms?'}
{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 It's time to treat drug addiction as a mental illness, not a crime."}
{'text': '\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 What about all the people who have been addicted to drugs since the time they were kids, and who are now in their 30s and 40s?'}

{'text': '\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 Like any other type of law, we need to view it as a tool to help individuals who are dependent on drugs to stay off of them, rather than a tool to punish people who...'}
{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 Just because something is harmful, doesn't mean we should ban it."}
{'text': "It's time to treat drug addiction as a mental illness, not a crime."}

{'text': '\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 In my opinion, I believe that legalizing drugs would lead to a situation where people would buy drugs illegally from dealers, rather than buying them from stores like Walgreens or CVS...'}

{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 Making drugs easier to get might actually make it easier for people to abuse them. For example, let's say that half the population were willing to try drugs, and half weren't."}
{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 Let's get our priorities straight. \xa0 We don't want to legalize drugs; we want to legalize the selling of drugs."}
{'text': "Reason #3: We don't need to care about the consequences of using drugs, we just need to care about the consequences of not using drugs."}

{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 Even if the current law had been in place prior to the introduction of the drug war, I don't think it would have made much of a difference in the amount of people who were..."}

{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 If you take away the state's right to tell you what you can do with your body, and if you remove the state's right to punish you if you break the law, then..."}
{'text': "If it makes things easier for people to use drugs, then by all means let's do it."}

{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 I don't feel the need to use substances in order to stay healthy; however, I do feel the need to keep my body in optimal condition."}
{'text': 'It is much easier to create new "legal products that people will want to consume than it is to enforce existing laws. In a sense, that is the entire point of the drug war.'}

{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 Because you can't arrest people who use drugs, there would be a greater incentive for people to do drugs."}
{'text': '\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 It will be difficult to change the image of drugs in the minds of many people, both now and later.'}

{'text': '\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 I personally do not think that drug use should be legalized, but I do think that people should be able to use drugs on their own terms.'}
{'text': '\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 All of us will have different opinions based on what we personally think is best.'}
{'text': "Wouldn't it be better for the whole world if we just didn't have any laws at all?"}

{'text': '\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 If there is going to be an effective way to combat drug abuse, it would be much more effective to find a way to prevent drug abuse from beginning in the first place.'}

{'text': '\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 There is no such thing as a simple answer. Some people will always want to use illegal drugs. There is no way for society to deal with that.'}
{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 The more people who say they're against legalization the more likely I am to start using drugs."}
{'text': '\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 Whether or not a drug is legal or illegal, the state has no right to tell me what I can and cannot do with my body.'}
{'text': 'The legalization of drugs has a lot more to do with economics than it does with morality.'}

{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 One of the reasons I got into drugs in the first place was because I didn't want to deal with the problems associated with being an addict."}

{'text': '\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 The massive majority of drugs sold in the US today are Schedule I drugs (which means they have the highest potential for abuse, no currently accepted medical use and a high potential for dependence and...'}

{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 I'd much rather legalize drugs because it gives us an opportunity to educate the public about the dangers of drugs (especially illegal drugs) as opposed to arresting more people and imprisoning more people..."}

{'text': '\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 Why not go the other way around? \xa0 Why not just legalize the buying and selling of drugs? \xa0 Why not legalize the trafficking of drugs?'}
{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 When I was a kid, I wasn't allowed to use drugs."}

{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 Even if we do legalize drugs, I don't believe that it's a good idea for us to do it without any serious attempts to treat drug addiction as a mental illness."}
{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 I don't think that people should be able to choose to consume drugs on their own terms."}
{'text': "Reason #4: I don't want the government to tell me what I can and can't do with my body!"}

{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 Why is it ok to make pot legal, but not ok to make heroin legal? Because it's far more addictive than marijuana, and because it's way more dangerous than heroin."}
{'text': '\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 It would be nice to see how it would affect the criminal records of people who have been arrested for drug offenses.'}
{'text': '\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 While I think legalization of drugs would be great, I am not 100% in favor of legalizing all drugs.'}

{'text': '\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 A lot of the stigma around drug use comes from the idea that it will lead to a violent death. However, most people will die early from prescription drug overdoses.'}
{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 If we were to legalize drugs, then we'd have to take away the public's right to arrest people for drug offenses."}
{'text': '\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 It sounds like a great idea to me. \xa0It might even solve so many of our problems. \xa0I really like the idea.'}
{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 If we legalize drugs, won't the government want to regulate and control what we're allowed to do with our bodies?"}
{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 We'd all be better off if people weren't made to feel guilty for using drugs, and people weren't punished for using drugs."}
{'text': '\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 The main goal of drug legalization is to eliminate the profits of the drug dealers.'}
{'text': '\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 The way I see it, there are a few things that we could probably do to mitigate the negative effects of drug use.'}
{'text': '\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 Please, whoever is reading this, please do more research before you ever propose legalizing drugs.'}

{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 In the long run, legalizing drugs might actually increase the harm done by drugs by making it much easier for people to get access to 'harder' drugs."}
{'text': "1. The most important thing is to prevent drug use. That's the most important responsibility of government, and the best way to prevent drug use would be to decriminalize drugs."}
{'text': 'The government has no business being in the business of regulating human behavior.'}
{'text': 'If the government were to allow the use of drugs, that would be a one-time deal. After that it would be a matter of public opinion.'}
{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 The vast majority of people who use drugs don't end up dead. \xa0Most of them die from prescription drug overdoses."}

{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 What would the world be like if people didn't have to worry about being arrested every time they use a drug?"}

{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 What if it wasn't so easy for the government to regulate the industry, and what if there was a degree of protection given to the populace from the excesses of the industry?"}

{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 This doesn't mean people shouldn't be free to use drugs. It just means they should be free from consequences related to their use of drugs."}
